<item>
            <title>[FELIX-3647] Component modification must continue if modify method throws</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-3647</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If the modify method of a Component throws an exception (and thus fails) the component modification must continue as if the modify method call succeeded; just an error message must be logged.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Currently, the component is deactivated and reactivated in this case thus being non-spec compliant&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(See Section 112.5.13, Modified Method in the Compendium R 4.3 specification)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
