                            <comment id="13447095" author="fmeschbe" created="Mon, 3 Sep 2012 02:56:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in Rev. 1380116 by passing a non-null MethodResult to be used if the called method throws.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus null is only returned from trying to call the modified method if no such method exists and thus the regular deactivation-activation cycle has to be used.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
